# function to count unique peptides and unique proteins
count_p <- function(){
  print(c(length(unique(raw_df$Sequence)), length(unique(raw_df$master_protein))))
}
  
# separate the filename into its component parts
raw_df <- raw_df %>%  separate(filename, sep="_", into = c("cell_line", "H", "L", "sample"), extra="drop")
raw_df$replicate <- substr(raw_df$sample, 5,5) # Extract the replicate number from the sample name

# Find the light and heavy quantification columns
light_column = colnames(raw_df)[grep("Abundance.F[0-9]+.Light.Sample", colnames(raw_df))]
heavy_column = colnames(raw_df)[grep("Abundance.F[0-9]+.Heavy.Sample", colnames(raw_df))]

# Select the columns we're interested in
raw_intensity <- raw_df %>% select("Sequence", "Modifications", "master_protein", light_column, heavy_column, "cell_line", "replicate")

colnames(raw_intensity)[4:5] <- c("Light","Heavy")  # rename columns

# Identify the NC & CL intensities given the label switching (Replicates 1 & 2, NC=Light, Replicates 3 & 4, NC=Heavy)
raw_intensity$NC <- ifelse(raw_intensity$replicate %in% c(1, 2), raw_intensity$Light, raw_intensity$Heavy)
raw_intensity$CL <- ifelse(raw_intensity$replicate %in% c(1, 2), raw_intensity$Heavy, raw_intensity$Light)

Step 2. Aggregate to peptide

agg_peptide <- raw_intensity %>%
  group_by(master_protein, Sequence, replicate)  %>%
  summarise(NC=sum(NC), CL=sum(CL))

# log2-transform the intensities
agg_peptide$NC <- log(agg_peptide$NC,2)
agg_peptide$CL <- log(agg_peptide$CL,2)
  
agg_peptide <- agg_peptide %>% mutate(Peptide_Ratio=CL-NC)

print(head(agg_peptide))

Let’s see if we have enough data to perform a t-test for differences at the peptide level. Here we will include all peptides for a protein across all replicates

runWilcox <- function(data){
  wc_test <- suppressMessages(wilcox.test(data$CL, data$NC, alternative="greater", paried=TRUE))
  return(data.frame("n_obs"=length(data$CL), "p.value"=wc_test$p.value))
}

sig_changes <- agg_peptide %>% filter(is.finite(Peptide_Ratio)) %>%
  group_by(master_protein) %>%
  filter(n()>2) %>%
  do(runWilcox(.))

### Load glycoprotein and GO_RBPs
glycoproteins <- readLines("../Data/glycoproteins.tsv")
RBPs <-readLines("../Data/GO_RBPs.tsv")
agg_protein_inc_wc <- agg_protein_inc_wc %>%
  mutate(GO_RBP=master_protein %in% RBPs, Glycoprotein=master_protein %in% glycoproteins) %>%
  mutate(Class = interaction(GO_RBP, Glycoprotein))

agg_protein_inc_wc$Class <- recode(factor(agg_protein_inc_wc$Class),
                                   "TRUE.FALSE"="RBP",
                                   "FALSE.TRUE"="Glycoprotein",
                                   "TRUE.TRUE"="RBGP",
                                   "FALSE.FALSE"="Putative RBP")

agg_protein_inc_wc$Class <- factor(agg_protein_inc_wc$Class, levels=c("RBP","Putative RBP", "Glycoprotein", "RBGP"))
p <- agg_protein_inc_wc %>% filter(Class!="RBGP") %>%
  mutate(sig=BH<0.05) %>%
  ggplot(aes(Protein_Ratio, colour=Class)) +
  geom_density() +
  scale_colour_discrete(name="") +
  my_theme +
  geom_vline(xintercept=0, linetype=2, colour="grey50")

print(p)

print(p + facet_grid(~sig))
